WEBVTT

00:03:57.532 --> 00:04:00.765
I mean, we'll be able to multiply
human intelligence trillions-fold

00:04:00.789 --> 00:04:03.236
before we run out of capacity.

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:06.085
CA: So this way of thinking allowed you --

00:04:06.109 --> 00:04:09.450
for example, in your book,
"The Age of Spiritual Machines,"

00:04:09.474 --> 00:04:14.047
you made a large number
of predictions about the future

00:04:14.071 --> 00:04:15.753
that surprised people at the time.

00:04:15.777 --> 00:04:17.219
RK: A hundred and forty-seven.

00:04:17.243 --> 00:04:18.777
CA: A hundred and forty-seven?

00:04:20.134 --> 00:04:22.835
So what percentage
of those actually came out?

00:04:23.415 --> 00:04:26.619
RK: You can Google
how my predictions are faring,

00:04:26.643 --> 00:04:30.518
and it analyzes those 147 predictions.